Welcome back to The Best & The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m Tara
Palmeri.

=C2=A0

We=E2=80=99re just days away from Donald Trump=E2=80=99s big bash, and it f=
eels very different than 2017, when both sides of the aisle were mourning =
=E2=80=9CAmerican Carnage,=E2=80=9D fretting over how the Trump carnival wo=
uld destroy #ThisTown, and canceling events in order to avoid the appearanc=
e of =E2=80=9Cnormalizing=E2=80=9D the unthinkable. This time around, titan=
s of industry, staffers, and K-Street slickers
are gearing up for all the typical inauguration weekend activities, hosting=
 a party=E2=80=94or better yet, crashing one=E2=80=94to try to grease the p=
alms of the new power elite.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

It=E2=80=99s always been a bit demeaning for those who were on the wrong si=
de of a messy primary. With enough alcohol and promises of financial suppor=
t, some grudges can be settled. Business leaders of the opposite party also=
 find their way to
reconciling with the new administration, with only lightly bruised egos. Bu=
t the wrath of Trump, and fear of retribution, have made these familiar rit=
