Hegseth=E2=80=99s Dry January
-----------------------

Pete Hegseth=E2=80=99s confirmation hearing for SecDef earlier today offere=
d
a glimpse into how G.O.P. senators are orienting themselves toward these hi=
gh-profile events=E2=80=94and also provided some clues about how Kash Patel=
, Tulsi Gabbard, and the rest of Trump=E2=80=99s controversial noms might p=
lay out. Given their 53-47 majority, Republicans are leveraging their upper=
 hand in every way possible, and that=E2=80=99s especially true when there=
=E2=80=99s a friendly chairman on the relevant committee, as was the case t=
oday with Mississippi=E2=80=99s
Roger Wicker at Armed Services. Across the dais, the Democrats appeared sob=
er, organized, and ready to resist=E2=80=94despite lacking the numbers. Her=
e=E2=80=99s the inside chatter=E2=80=A6

* Spotlight on Ernst: It didn=E2=80=99t surprise anyone that Iowa=E2=80=99s=
 Joni Ernst, the Senate Republican most openly skeptical about Hegseth=E2=
=80=99s nomination, conducted the most pointed questioning among her party =
colleagues. Still, she framed her inquiries as if she were trying to get to=
 yes=E2=80=94she extracted assurances, for instance, that Hegseth would =E2=
=80=9Cappoint a senior-level official dedicated to sexual assault preventio=
n and response.=E2=80=9D Those tells
proved correct within hours, when she announced in a one-sentence statement=
 to Fox News that she would vote for Hegseth. Wicker took a similar tack, a=
llowing Hegseth to answer the most severe allegations against him on his ow=
n terms. (The former Fox News anchor again denounced the allegations as a =
=E2=80=9Ccoordinated smear campaign=E2=80=9D by the =E2=80=9Cleft-wing medi=
a.=E2=80=9D)

When Democratic senators interrogated Hegseth, Wicker responded with proced=
ural pushback by submitting a letter of support relevant to the
line of questioning. Wicker also limited their questioning to one round, de=
spite ranking member Jack Reed=E2=80=99s objection. (Exhausted witnesses ar=
e more likely to make mistakes.) In the end, most of the G.O.P. senators fr=
amed Hegseth as a redeemed man and the victim of media slander.
* Kelly=E2=80=99s antihero: Despite broader existential despair about their=
 party=E2=80=99s leadership, Armed Services Dems seemed to have their act t=
ogether, with each
member homing in on a single topic and moving as quickly as possible throug=
h questions in their allotted seven minutes. To a person, these sessions we=
re a beatdown for Hegseth, but it was America=E2=80=99s Stepdad ( https://t=
ime.com/4468126/tim-kaine-stephen-colbert-late-show-stepdad/?utm_campaign=
=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F14%2F25%29&utm_content=
=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F14%2F25%29&utm_medium=3D=
email_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), Virg=
inia=E2=80=99s Tim Kaine, who conducted the most ruthless and specific inte=
rrogation of Hegseth=E2=80=99s character, dwelling on allegations that the
nominee sexually assaulted a woman in Monterey, California, in 2017. =E2=80=
=9CHoly shit,=E2=80=9D texted one Kaine alumnus. Another seasoned Democrati=
c operative texted me, =E2=80=9CTim Kaine has no effs left to give. Just lo=
ok at his hair.=E2=80=9D And yet, of all the questioners, it was Mark Kelly=
, a Navy man, who got to the nub of the hearing: =E2=80=9CHave you overcome=
 personal issues=E2=80=94or are you the target of a smear campaign? It can=
=E2=80=99t be both.=E2=80=9D
* The weeks
ahead: Beyond Ernst, none of the swingy Republican senators=E2=80=94Susan C=
ollins, John Curtis, Lisa Murkowski, etcetera=E2=80=94sit on Armed Services=
=2E So the fawning Republican performan=
ces earlier today might not be represe=
ntative of how the rest of the confirmation hearings might play out. On the=
 other hand, one Democrat I spoke with conceded that Hegseth will likely be=
 confirmed, before summing up what the minority party
achieved today: =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re showing why he shouldn=E2=80=99t.=E2=
=80=9D

