ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong><em>Tara Palmeri</em></strong><strong>:=
 What do you think
about the possibility of Trump holding back support for California and its =
relief efforts once he=E2=80=99s sworn in, because it=E2=80=99s considered =
a sanctuary state and likely to push back on efforts to deport undocumented=
 immigrants?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>Ken Cuccinelli</em>: I don=E2=
=80=99t think there=E2=80=99s <em>ever </em>a legitimate basis for any stat=
e or locality <em>not</em> to at least be cooperative. They don=E2=80=99t h=
ave to offer their
own people and resources, but they need to at least cooperate in letting th=
e federal government accomplish its role in immigration law. I also don=E2=
=80=99t think it=E2=80=99s appropriate to make emergency support decisions =
based on other issues that are going on. I think both sides in that discuss=
ion are off-base to a certain extent. I=E2=80=99d rather there wasn=E2=80=
=99t crossover on these things. But let=E2=80=99s face it, President Donald=
 Trump writes his own rule book on these things. And sometimes that works t=
o the advantage of
people like <strong>Gavin Newsom</strong>; it did during Covid. And sometim=
es it does not, as it appears right now with respect to the wildfires.</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;"><strong>Donald Trump was specific when he said on day one, =
he=E2=80=99s going to conduct the largest deportation of all time. Do you t=
hink that=E2=80=99s possible?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
m:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">What will
happen to implement that commitment is that all of the presidential instruc=
tions that are necessary to commence large-scale deportation will be <em>si=
gned</em> on day one. Does that mean 5,000 ICE agents are suddenly going to=
 deport 10 million people in one day? No, it doesn=E2=80=99t mean that. But=
 it does mean the presidential authority to commence that effort will begin=
 on day one. Will there be refinements <em>after</em> day one? Absolutely.=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Do you think there will be=
 any activity on day one besides the order?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:=
0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Th=
e key activity will be at the border itself. So yes, there will be actual a=
ctivity on day one, but the activity will be the first steps=E2=80=94actual=
 <em>steps</em>, not just orders=E2=80=94of sealing the border. And by seal=
ing the border, I mean [sealing it] to illegal traffic, particularly
between the legal ports of entry. We have a nearly 2,000-mile border with M=
exico, and, of course, only a few points of legal entry into the United Sta=
tes.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">That doesn=E2=80=99t mean it will be close=
d on day one, but you=E2=80=99ll see actual deployment of individuals. From=
 the moment Donald Trump is sworn in as president, border patrol goes from =
20,000 greeters who are executing a catch-and-release plan, by and
large=E2=80=94that=E2=80=99s been reduced a bit the last few months=E2=80=
=94to actual <em>enforcers</em> of the border.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:=
0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><s=
trong>Who are these people who will be securing the border? Existing Border=
 Patrol agents who are sitting on the sidelines? Or the military? I mean, y=
ou need money for people to go to the border and actually seal it off=E2=80=
=A6</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">You don=E2=80=99t need money for the Border Patrol agen=
ts, because you=E2=80=99ve already budgeted it, and now you=E2=80=99re just=
 cutting them loose to actually perform the mission of the Border Patrol, w=
hich is to patrol the border instead of being greeters, as I refer to them.=
 That=E2=80=99s a very dramatic change. You go from 20,000 helping people i=
n, to 20,000 keeping people out=E2=80=94a 40,000-person swing with no chang=
e in the budget. I also fully expect deployment of military members on the =
border very
quickly; I think some of the orders you see issued on day one will be to de=
ploy military members to the border between the legal ports of entry. And u=
nlike the first Trump administration, and the <strong>Biden</strong> admini=
stration, where they backed up the border patrol and provided reconnaissanc=
e but didn=E2=80=99t do any confronting of people entering the country, I t=
hink the military will be used in Trump=E2=80=99s second term to actually s=
top people from entering in the first place.</p><p style=3D"margin:
0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><s=
trong>Is it legal to use the military? Why didn=E2=80=99t Trump do it durin=
g the first term?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The question of its legalit=
y isn=E2=80=99t, in my view, why it wasn=E2=80=99t utilized earlier; it was=
 the reluctance to use the military. And, as you heard Donald Trump in the =
campaign, he is over that reluctance.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom=
:0px;">=C2=A0
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Do you expect the cour=
ts to try to stop that=E2=80=94for example, a California injunction?</stron=
g></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">They can=E2=80=99t stop that.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><s=
trong>They were able to stop the Muslim ban for a long time. Trump=E2=80=99=
s side eventually won, but they were able to hold up a number of other
orders=E2=80=A6</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0=
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">It=E2=80=99s interesting that the second Trump t=
erm will benefit from a lot of that litigation having already happened in t=
he first Trump term. That=E2=80=99s the law of the land now. And the Muslim=
 ban, as you referred to it=E2=80=94of course, it involved more countries t=
han just Islamic countries, but that was the press name for it=E2=80=94was =
upheld. That=E2=80=99s been litigated. And at the Supreme Court level, that=
=E2=80=99s an immigration law
authority. When you deploy the military, that [falls under] the [Commander-=
in-Chief Clause] of Article II in the Constitution, which gives the preside=
nt authority to secure the country. He doesn=E2=80=99t have to let anybody =
in between the legal ports of entry, under any circumstances, and he can de=
ploy the military to stop the invasion.</p></div>
